  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba9\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd 6 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "6 Tamil Nadu fishermen arrested",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Yesterday (20) Sri Lankan Navy arrested a fishing boat and 6 fishermen from Rameswaram for fishing across the border and took them to the Thalaimannar Naval Camp for investigation.",
        "Fishermen in more than 400 barges from Rameswaram fishing port got fishing permits and came to the sea to fish.",
        "While the fishermen were fishing between Thalaimannar and Nachiguda last night, the Sri Lankan Navy patrolling the area arrested two boats and 11 fishermen for catching fish across the border.",
        "After the fisherman reported that a boat and 5 fishermen from it had come across the border due to mechanical failure, the Sri Lankan Navy inspected the boat and sent the boat and 5 fishermen back to Tamil Nadu after confirming the mechanical failure.",
        "In this case, the Sri Lankan Navy arrested another boat belonging to an ambassador from Thangachi Math and six fishermen namely Balamurugan, Anthony, Thangapandi, Ajith, Krishnan and Maduku Pichai with the boat for catching fish across the border and brought them to the Thalaimannar Naval Camp and conducted an investigation.",
        "After the first phase of interrogation conducted by the Sri Lankan Navy on the captive Rameswaram fishermen, the 6 fishermen will be handed over to the Mannar Fisheries Department officials and will be produced in the Mannar court.",
        "Rameswaram All Barge Fishermen's Association fishermen have requested the central and state governments media Sri Lankan government to immediately release the captive fishermen and boats."
      ],
